\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.3}{\ignorespaces Degree 1 B-Spline Formation. Top left is a series of time shifted degree 1 B-Spline basis functions overlapping. Bottom left is the sum of all basis functions from the above. Top middle plots the control points in red, with the correspondingly scaled and time shifted basis functions. Bottom middle is the sum of all basis functions. Right plots are identical to middle plots, except with the index $5$ control point changed from $1.5$ to $2$.}}{47}{figure.caption.36}%
